The mean is the arithmetic average of a set of values. It is calculated by summing all the values in the dataset and dividing by the total number of values. The mean provides a measure of central tendency, which provides the “average” value in a dataset.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \text {Mean} \ (\bar{x}) = \frac{\sum \limits _{i=1}^{n} x_i}{n} \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$x_i=\big ((a_i,b_i,c_i); \ \varrho _i, \ \varsigma _i, \ \xi _i \big ), \ i=1,2,\ldots ,n,$$\end{document}
n is the total number of elements in the set.

